Honolulu, Hawaii 96813 Honolulu, Hawaii 96813
Aloha Senate President Kouchi and Speaker Nakamura:
Arbitration awards (University of Hawaii and other State Executive Branch
departments) have been issued concerning United Public Workers (UPW) class action
grievances for Units 1 (Blue Collar Employees) and 10 (Institutional, Health, and
Correctional Workers) relating to temporary hazard pay (THP) during the COVID-19
pandemic. Funding was provided for these awards by Act 29, SLH 2025. However, the
appropriations are insufficient to cover the balance of requirements, so additional
funding is being requested. Additionally, the supplemental award issued for employees
of the other State Executive Branch departments is final. The amounts do not include
funding for an agreement or arbitration award for the Department of Education, as not
all matters have been resolved.
The following is a summary of the included and excluded requirements of the arbitration
awards for the current fiscal biennium being transmitted to the Legislature for
appropriation:

-2-
FY 26
Salaries and Fringe
General $66,795,019
Interdepartmental Transfers 306,532
Revolving 203,736
Total $67,305,287
Attached are proposed drafts Senate Bill No. 3090, S.D. 2, and House Bill No. 2271,
H.D. 2, which have been updated to reflect the above noted estimated collective
bargaining amounts.
Mahalo,
Josh Green, M.D.
Governor, State of Hawaii
Attachments
c: Honorable Donovan M. Dela Cruz
Honorable Chris Todd

