THIRTY-THIRD LEGISLATURE, 2026
STATE OF HAWAII
PROPOSED
A BILL FORAN ACT
MAKING EMERGENCY APPROPRIATIONS FOR PUBLIC EMPLOYMENT COST
ITEMS.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 PART I
2 SECTION 1. This Act is recommended by the governor for
3 immediate passage in accordance with section 9 of article VII of
4 the Constitution of the State of Hawaii.
5 PART II
6 SECTION 2. There are appropriated or authorized from the
7 sources of funding indicated below to collective bargaining
8 statewide (BUF 102) the following sums or so much thereof as may
9 be necessary for fiscal year 2025-2026 to fund collective
10 bargaining cost items associated with grievances filed under
11 agreements negotiated with the exclusive representative of
12 collective bargaining units (1) and (10), and for their excluded
13 counterparts. The amounts are for arbitration awards for the
14 university of Hawaii and other executive branch departments
15 related to temporary hazard pay. These amounts are in addition
16 to the amounts provided in Act 29, Session Laws of Hawaii 2025:

Page 2 2271
H.B. NO.
H.D. 2
PROPOSED
1 FY 2025-2026
2 General funds $66,795,019
3 Interdepartmental transfers 306,532
4 Revolving funds 203,736
5 SECTION 3. Funds appropriated or authorized by this part
6 shall be allotted by the director of finance to the appropriate
7 state departments for expenditure in fiscal year 2025-2026 for
8 the purposes of this part.
9 PART III
10 SECTION 4. Salary increases and cost adjustments provided
11 in this Act for any officer or employee whose compensation is
12 paid, in whole or in part, from federal, special, or other funds
13 shall be paid wholly or proportionately, as the case may be,
14 from the respective funds; provided that if the respective funds
15 are unable to support such payments, appropriations from other
16 means of financing may be used with the approval of the
17 Governor.
18 SECTION 5. Funds appropriated or authorized by this Act
19 that are not expended or encumbered by June 30, 2026, shall
20 lapse as of that date.
21 SECTION 6. This Act shall take effect upon its approval.

